{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17411343","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17411343"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T06:23:32+09:30","options":[2],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T06:23:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260985"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260985"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"38"}},"bookmark":{"data":{"type":"bookmarks","id":"1210294"}}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17470901","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17470901"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T21:42:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T21:42:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"38"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260985","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1260985"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T06:22:58+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T06:24:33+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":1,"questionsAnswered":1,"marksTotal":1,"marksAttainable":1,"marksAttempted":1,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T06:23:32+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"38","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/38"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0,0.01,0.28,0.57]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"38"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"48677"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"38","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/38"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"38"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"33622"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"42"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"9641"},{"type":"tags","id":"11631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8454"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8764"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13190"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44014"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"48677","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/48677"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 4-year-old boy presents to the General Practice clinic with his mother who is concerned that her son may have Marfan syndrome, as she has an 8-year-old daughter with the condition. She asks if there is a screening test that could be done to exclude this condition in her family members. The boy has no significant medical history and is up to date with immunisations. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial approach to screen for Marfan syndrome in this child?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Transthoracic echocardiography","MRI spine","Chest X-ray","Genetic analysis for fibrillin-1 gene mutation","Clinical evaluation using the Revised Ghent criteria"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate initial approach to screen for Marfan syndrome in this child is \u003Cstrong\u003Eclinical evaluation using the Revised Ghent criteria\u003C/strong\u003E. These criteria are the current standard for diagnosing Marfan syndrome and can be used as an initial screening tool for family members of affected individuals.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe Revised Ghent criteria (2010) consider the following:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPresence of ectopic lens\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAortic root dilation (Z-score \u2265 2) or aortic root dissection\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESystemic features (scored based on specific clinical findings)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EFamily history\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn individuals with a positive family history of Marfan syndrome in a first-degree relative (as this patient has), the diagnosis can be made if one of the following criteria is met:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EEctopic lens\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EAortic root dilation with a Z-score \u2265 2 or aortic root dissection\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EA systemic score \u2265 7 points\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETransthoracic echocardiography\u003C/strong\u003E is an important investigation in Marfan syndrome to assess aortic root dilation, but it is not the most appropriate initial screening approach. It would typically be performed as part of the clinical evaluation if indicated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMRI spine\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Echest X-ray\u003C/strong\u003E are not initial screening tools for Marfan syndrome. They may be used to evaluate specific features (such as dural ectasia or pneumothorax) if clinically indicated, but are not part of the initial screening process.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenetic analysis for fibrillin-1 gene mutation\u003C/strong\u003E is not recommended as an initial screening tool. While over 90% of patients with Marfan syndrome have an FBN1 mutation, genetic testing is typically reserved for specific circumstances, such as when it will change management, facilitate family screening, or aid in prenatal diagnosis. Even with a positive genetic test, the diagnosis still requires fulfillment of clinical criteria.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical evaluation using the Revised Ghent criteria allows for a comprehensive assessment of the child\u0027s features and family history, providing a structured approach to screening for Marfan syndrome. This evaluation may then guide further investigations or referrals as needed.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The Revised Ghent criteria are used for the diagnosis of Marfan syndrome, considering ectopic lens, aortic root dilation/dissection, and systemic features.","Clinical evaluation using the Revised Ghent criteria is the initial approach for screening family members for Marfan syndrome."],"references":["Wright MJ, Connolly HM. Genetics, clinical features, and diagnosis of Marfan syndrome and related disorders. In: Dietz HC, Yeon SB, editors. UpToDate. [Internet]. Waltham (MA): UpToDate Inc; 2023. [updated 2022 April 29; cited 2023 Mar 20]. Available from: https://www.uptodate.com/contents/genetics-clinical-features-and-diagnosis-of-marfan-syndrome-and-related-disorders?search=marfan%20syndrome\u0026source=search_result\u0026selectedTitle=1~150\u0026usage_type=default\u0026display_rank=1#H1892694222"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"33622"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"38"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"33622","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/33622"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-07-15T19:10:41+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-07-15T19:10:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"38"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"48677"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paedia